thread.title: Another win for Lady Bulldogs

title: Another win for Lady Bulldogs
text: Another win for Lady Bulldogs Comment The Carmi Times - Carmi, IL Writer Posted Oct. 9, 2015 at 11:00 AM Updated at 11:04 AM Posted Oct. 9, 2015 at 11:00 AM Updated at 11:04 AM CARMI – The CWC Lady Bulldogs crept closer to the BDC East title with a 25-12, 25-18 victory over the Eldorado Eagles on Thursday. The Lady Bulldogs moved their conference record to 8-0 and can assure themselves at least a tie for the title with a win at Vienna on Tuesday. CWC dominated Game 1. Eldorado called their first timeout after a kill by Abby Vaughan gave the Lady Bulldogs an 8-0 lead. The score was 13-2 and only Peighton Parks and Vaughan had served by the time Lixi Wheeler was able to enter the game on her regular rotation into the front line. The lead grew to 20-3 before Eldorado called their second timeout. They stopped CWC’s momentum for a time and came back to 24-12 before a dig from Paige Winter, a set by Maggi Ackerman and a kill from Wheeler ended Game 1. Game 2 played more evenly at evenly at the start with CWC only clinging to a 12-11 lead before they began the game-clinching run. Good passing a strong play at the net moved the lead to 20-13 and eventually to a 25-18 final. The Carmi Times - Carmi, IL Writer Posted Oct. 9, 2015 at 11:00 AM Updated at 11:04 AM
